# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback. Existing static files (assets, /sitemap.xml,
# /robots.txt, /llms.txt, icons) are served first; any other path falls through
# to the app shell so client-side routes (/docs, /compare/*, /alternatives/*,
# /uses/*, /app) resolve on a direct hit or refresh. Status 200 = rewrite, so
# the URL the visitor sees is preserved (important for SEO).

# Retired page — the Astryx theme-generator use case (the Astryx export was
# dropped to keep the export on the core). 301 to the closest live equivalent.
# Specific rule sits ABOVE the catch-all so it wins (first match).
/uses/astryx-theme-generator   /uses/design-system-generator   301

# Retired /templates marketing page — folded into /showcases ("seed a starting
# screen"). EXACT match only, so the CLI's static /templates/<name>.html files +
# /templates/index.json still serve directly (a /templates/* wildcard would eat them).
/templates            /showcases   301
/templates/preview/*  /showcases   301

/*    /index.html   200
